@retardoface

Have listened to your work and it's really well done, only one thing, the sound level is unfortunately pumping quite much when a crescendo or bass thump occurs, too sad because your intention and effort is well appreciated.
I really like the extended and airy sound of the cymbals, one of the most difficult instruments to reproduce because of its complex and high frequency nature, I wonder if the high frequency was a bit elevated but nothing that disturbed. 

Thanks so much for you work!
9x better than any CD I've ever heard. Bob is smoking & smiling on this cut.
